356 class Control
357 {
358 public:
359 Edu totalDur{};
360 Evpu totalWidth{};
361 Evpu minWidth{};
362 Evpu allotWidth{};
363
364 static const xml::XmlElementArray<Control>& xmlMappingArray();
365 };
366
367 // Populated only when the XML node includes a <control> element
368 std::shared_ptr<Control> control;
369
370 // Populated for standard beat entries (inci > 0)
371 Edu dur{};
372 Evpu pos{};
373 Evpu endPos{};
374 Evpu minPos{};
375
376 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
377 {
378 OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
379 if (control && getInci() != 0) {
380 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has a control instance in inci " + std::to_string(*getInci()));
381 }
382 if (getInci() == 0 && !control) {
383 control = std::make_shared<Control>();
384 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Beat chart for measure " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " is missing its control instance.");
385 }
386 }
387
388 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "beatChart";
389 static const xml::XmlElementArray<BeatChartElement>& xmlMappingArray();

538class FontDefinition : public OthersBase
539{
540 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC = 0xfff; // (4095)
541 static constexpr uint32_t SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN = 2;
542
543public:
545 explicit FontDefinition(const DocumentWeakPtr& document, Cmper partId, ShareMode shareMode, Cmper cmper)
546 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper) {}
547
550 enum class CharacterSetBank
551 {
552 MacOS,
553 Windows
554 };
555
556 // Public properties corresponding to the XML structure
557 CharacterSetBank charsetBank{};
558 int charsetVal{};
563 int pitch{};
564 int family{};
565 std::string name;
566
580 bool calcIsSymbolFont() const
581 {
582 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::MacOS && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_MAC) {
583 return true;
584 }
585 if (charsetBank == CharacterSetBank::Windows && charsetVal == SYMBOL_CHARSET_WIN) {
586 return true;
587 }
588 return false;
589 }
590
591 constexpr static std::string_view XmlNodeName = "fontName";
592 static const xml::XmlElementArray<FontDefinition>& xmlMappingArray();
593};

608class Frame : public OthersBase

613 : OthersBase(document, partId, shareMode, cmper, inci) {}
614
615 EntryNumber startEntry{};

618
622 bool iterateRawEntries(std::function<bool(const MusxInstance<Entry>& entry)> iterator) const;
623
628 MusxInstanceList<Entry> getEntries() const;
629
630 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
631 {
632 this->OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
633 if (startTime && (startEntry || endEntry)) {
634 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has non-zero startTime and non-zero startEntry or endEntry.");
635 }
636 if (!startTime && !startEntry) {
637 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no start entry.");
638 }
639 if (!startTime && !endEntry) {
640 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Frame " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " has no end entry.");
641 }
642 }

762 class StringInfo

770 };

780 ClefIndex speedyClef{};

782 void integrityCheck(const std::shared_ptr<Base>& ptrToThis) override
783 {
784 this->OthersBase::integrityCheck(ptrToThis);
785 if (numStrings != int(strings.size())) {
786 MUSX_INTEGRITY_ERROR("Fret instrument " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " specifies " + std::to_string(numStrings)
787 + " strings but has " + std::to_string(strings.size()) + " StringInfo instances.");
788 }
789 if (!fretSteps.empty() && numFrets != int(fretSteps.size())) {
790 util::Logger::log(util::Logger::LogLevel::Info, "Fret instrument " + std::to_string(getCmper()) + " specifies " + std::to_string(numFrets)
791 + " frets but has " + std::to_string(fretSteps.size()) + " diatonic fret steps specified.");
792 }
793 }

796 static const xml::XmlElementArray<FretInstrument>& xmlMappingArray();
